				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Mayhex!" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mayhex! possibly the greatest and most addictive fantasy card game ever created - coming soon from Thornway Games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Taken from the Celtic portmanteau of mayhe&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;m (a situation where there is little or no order or control) and hex (a wicked spell or curse which brings bad luck), Mayhex! basically means trouble!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mayhex! is a fantasy based zombie survival card game (for 2 - 8 players (the more the better), aged 13+) which features a new game mechanic - you are able (amongst other actions) to Dice Duel or Coin Duel via the cards, so no real dice or coins are required to play the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Objective:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The object of the game is to be the first to gain 100 points; only then will you be able to cure the zombie virus and save yourself.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Things are never quite that easy though, are they? Especially when there are Goblins stealing your equipment, Undead hunting in the catacombs and Mayhex! magic getting in the way.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each pack consists of a deck of 108 unique cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Every card has two dice (scores ranging from 2 to 12) and a coin (either a Head or Tails) printed on it (to enable you to Dice Duel or Coin Duel). You don't require anything else to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mayhex!'s 108 unique playing cards consist of Positive Cards, Negative Cards, Action Cards, Mayhex! Cards, Infection Cards, and Uninfected Cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Like any good card game, Mayhex! requires both skill and a touch of luck to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of your turn you must select a card from the Well. You must play one card from your Hand on either yourself, into the Pit or more enjoyably into another player's Lab.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How your friends will laugh when you make them Dice Duel to see if their entire Hand must be placed directly into the Pit or maybe you&amp;rsquo;ll give them minus 25 points or better yet, an Infected Card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We'll be uploading how to play Mayhex! tutorial videos to the Thornway Games website in late February 2015. (Pro tip number 1 is: learn the cards!)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
